---

## Code Smells Addressed

| Smell | Before | After |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Hardcoded config | Module-level constants (`DB_PASS = "password123"`) | `Config` dataclass loaded from `PIPELINE_*` env vars via `Config.from_env()` |
| SQL injection | `"... VALUES ('%s', '%s', %d)" % (dt, msg, count)` | Parameterized `conn.execute("INSERT INTO errors VALUES (?, ?, ?)", (now, msg, count))` |
| God function | Single 80-line `proc_data()` doing everything | 9 focused functions following Extract → Transform → Load |
| Fragile parsing | `line.split(" ")` with index magic and `in` checks | 3 compiled regex patterns (`_LOG_LINE_RE`, `_USER_EVENT_RE`, `_API_CALL_RE`) |
| No types/docs | Cryptic vars (`d_list`, `r`, `s`, `m`), no annotations | Typed dataclasses (`ErrorEntry`, `UserEvent`, `ApiCall`, `WarningEntry`, `ParsedLog`), type hints + docstrings on all 9 public functions |
| Bare `open`/`close` | `f = open(LOG_FILE, "r"); ...; f.close()` | `with log_file.open() as f:` context manager |

## Techniques Applied

- **Extract Method** — `proc_data` decomposed into `extract_log_entries` / `_parse_line`, `compute_error_summary`, `compute_api_latency`, `compute_active_sessions`, `load_error_metrics`, `load_api_metrics`, `render_report`, `write_report`
- **Introduce Parameter Object** — Hardcoded constants → `Config(frozen=True)` dataclass
- **Replace Magic String with Named Type** — Untyped dicts → frozen dataclasses
